flowRoot.flowPara: Controls the hormonal system of the human body, can be influencet with chemical substances, as well as with conditioning, sport...

The hypophysis (gr. Ὑπόφυσις hypóphysis) is a hormonal gland, which plays a central role in the regulation of the hormone system in the body. It is a kind of interface with which the brain regulates the release of hormonal processes such as growth, reproduction and other metabolisms
